# Dev hot-sync manifest: repo_path|install_path|systemd_unit (unit optional)
# Used by scripts/dev-pull.sh against scripts/dev-serve.sh on the build host.
#
# Source of truth for Maps/CC hot-sync is packages/… (NOT config/includes.chroot/…).
# Chroot copies are for ISO builds only; editing them alone will not show up after pull.
#
# Command Centre:
#   - Serves UI from /usr/lib/atlas/command_centre_ui.html (loaded once at process start → restart)
#   - Serves Maps from /usr/share/atlas/maps-viewer via http://127.0.0.1:8787/maps/
# After maps-viewer files are pulled, dev-pull.sh re-runs sync-nomad-maps.sh (NOMAD /srv copy)
# and restarts atlas-command-centre.service once.
#
packages/atlas-command-centre/usr/lib/atlas/command_centre.py|/usr/lib/atlas/command_centre.py|atlas-command-centre.service
packages/atlas-command-centre/usr/lib/atlas/command_centre_ui.html|/usr/lib/atlas/command_centre_ui.html|atlas-command-centre.service
packages/atlas-command-centre/usr/lib/atlas/chat_store.py|/usr/lib/atlas/chat_store.py|atlas-command-centre.service
